caption: Not familiar with Gainesville and were visiting a museum at UF. Randomly searching for a place for lunch and stopped here. It’s a bar atmosphere but very quiet at lunch. The employee was wearing a mask which is important to me.  The food was quick and delicious! Some of the best fish tacos I’ve ever had and very inexpensive. All of us loved what we ordered. I would definitely go back.

Been twice now. Nothing bad but nothing really special. Just a bar with some food. Do like the nachos. Large portion. 6 drinks + nachos = $80. No table service. Is that due to covid? (Lol). Trying to catch up with friends and had to keep leaving the table to stand and wait at the bar.
Open late night if you're hungry in the middle of the night. Vegan options available! Food was good!

Great food at great prices! They have a nice variety of items on the menu for everyone - tacos, burgers, sandwiches. We went here for drinks/dinner, and we enjoyed everything we got! We had a burger and our friend got the spicy chicken sandwich. I’m not big on spicy, but the feedback I heard from the sandwich suggests it tastes like Nashville hot chicken. If you’re looking for a good spot to hang with friends and enjoy good food, this is the place to be. They also had good happy hour deals!
Wonderful. Definitely the best bar I’ve been to in Gainesville yet ♥️ The food is so yummy and there are lots of wonderful drinks. Great vibe and outdoor seating too.
You’ve read it before. Best burger in Gainesville. Yes, better than Mac’s. No you’re wrong.
Always a cool place for hanging out after work. Crispy squid tacos were yummy.

Literally everything we ordered, food and drink, was great here. Loved the banh mi hotdogs, burgers, and tacos. All of the 3 different rounds of cocktails each of us got were unique and really good. 10/10 recommend.
This was a different type of establishment, but the food and drinks were great.  I chose the baby burger and nachos.  I stayed until they kicked me out.
Knowledge staff with a good hand for pouring drinks. Fries are also pretty clutch too.
Take a step back into time where bartenders know how to make classic old school cocktails.  As chef's are to food, their bartenders are to cocktails! Enjoy!!!!!

This place is great. Cool vibe, great cocktails with wide selection (some among the best I've had), and really good elevated bar food (not super fancy, but definitely above typical food for such an establishment).  Our favorites were the Yuca Fries (Curry Aioli for the win!), crispy squid tacos, and the Banh Mi Hot Dog - all really well done and creative.  Did not know that places like this would exist in Gainesville, but so happy to see it! This place would do well in any city - Bravo!
Food is meh alcohol is alright. Awesome for a bar
this place is the best food ever and my uncle owns it so eat it NOW!!!
Their drinks are great. Their staff can sometimes be standoff-ish. Either way it's a good place
Delicious!!

Visited this place for the first time yesterday. The atmosphere at the place is great and the food is phenomenal! Also, the drinks were very nicely done and the prices were very reasonable. Great spot to hang out.
Raw oysters (cold water varieties), buttery conch fritters (with lotsa conch) and herb-infused libations - I’m a customer for life.

My best friend and I loved this place!  Our original plan was to go to have some drinks at another place but we were so glad we saw this on our way and ended up at cry baby’s. Finding parking was a challenge on a Friday night. But Food was delicious. Atmosphere was chill. Cocktails were perfect (the bartender is amazing). Music selection was just right. Great customer service. Will definitely be visiting again soon.

GET THE SPICY CHICKEN SANDWICH! It's life-changing. Also, the atmosphere is so cool. It's got a very Havana, Soflo vibe and they play records for their background music. The place it just great and the people are so friendly. I can't wait to go back.
What am I gonna cry about?
Good drinks. Amazing burger.
Cool vibes. Food was.. ok. Decent wine selection.
Loved the veggie burger. Fries were fresh 😀
A great place in downtown Gainesville to get a drink. If you love people watching, grab a seat outside on their patio and enjoy!
Drink was good but expensive. Tried ordering fries at 959 and said the kitchen was close.d
Their food and drinks are so tasty. Great, knowledgeable staff.

This another great craft-cocktail bar in Gainesville. Their drinks tend to be a little more alcohol forward but are still delicious. This is a larger space, great for groups. It definitely can be busy, especially during prime times, but I've usually been able to squeeze into a spot at the bar or a seat.
Excellent bartenders, delicious drinks and food.

I was so excited to see Cry Baby's open from the afternoon restaurant advertising it a year or two ago. The name is unique. The drinks are good. The food/snacks are yummy. I've worked here, but got a different job in another industry. They're great to work with and chill, but clean and professional too!  Great bar and atmosphere. The menu has grown a LOT since they have opened. The bartenders are great and make wonderful drinks. Be sure to tip them extra!!! This has turned out to be one of my favorite spots to get a drink in Gainesville now.
The food and drinks were great, and I loved the atmosphere. The people who worked there are so nice, and me and my friend had a great time.

Wow. The blonde bartender was extremely slow and had an attitude. Horrible customer service. We spent hundreds of dollars celebrating our bride who’s getting married this weekend and the staff was extremely rude and was trying to kick us out at 1:55am on a Friday night. And when questioned, stating it closed at 2, we were rudely addressed and received horrible customer service as we were demanded to chug our expensive drinks WE ALREADY PAID FOR. Completely unprofessional, inconsiderate, and inappropriate.
I spent the whole night here and I was waiting for my Uber and they wouldn’t let us go back inside at 1:45 to use the rest room. Poor customer service. I won’t be coming back
The food and drinks are delicious with a fun spin. The location is fantastic and it's a good place to hangout. Definitely one of our stops when we bar hop.
A little pricey but the drinks and vibes are good
Good drinks that are well made and great burgers. There's also good happy hour specials. My only complaint is that it can be hard to hear conversation in there if it's full.
Surprisingly awesome burger. Crispy but in a good satisfying way. Chicken sandwich is actually spicy as advertised.
Not worth going to this place, the bartender was very rude and unprofessional

DO NOT GO HERE. For real. I went with a group of international students, and the bartenders treated them horribly and MOCKED THEM for how they spoke English. I’m serious, this place is not even worth it. Don’t go here. Completely appalled and disgusted by what happened here.
Bad place to visit, they discriminate people

Love the atmosphere and fantastic cocktails.  The music is always great too. But the food is the best part. Hands down best burger and chicken burger I've had in town. The banh mi veggie hot dog is amazing. Their chef knows what they're doing.  It's become popular and can get packed after 9 pm so get there early if you want a table.

Brilliant craft cocktails with super dope pub food.  The Big Baby Burger and mountains of perfectly salty fries are my goto dish here, the caramelized onions are to die for. However, I must come in with a very empty stomach because there is so much to eat it can be overwhelming if I'm not ready for it.  The cocktails are not overly adventurous, but they are put together with class and care. Great for a traditional drink, think Old Fashioned, Tom Collins, Moscow Mule, Mai Tai, that sort of thing. No crazy experimental drinks with cryptic names, just solid skillful drinks at reasonable prices. Love it.
Excellent food, drinks, and service in an upscape casual atmosphere.
Always busy, but a great bar with great cocktails.

This cute little place is just a few doors up from the river and a popular spot. We had the breakfast sandwich of egg, bacon and cheese on an English muffin, and the Avocado toast. The fresh avocado spread had a splash of olive oil and pinch of sea salt, delicious. The coffee was good, but they ran out fresh squeezed orange juice by the time we got there at 10:30. Our Four Square bill came to $16 with counter service tip for above mentioned items.

I gave two stars because the bar tender was pleasant and she cares about her craft. This review is not a reflection of the service. But the food was NASTY. The nachos should have been served in a bowl with a spoon because it was bean soup in a basket. The veggie burger was awful. Dont call that tzatziki, it's dill flavored mayonnaise drowning a flavorless veggie patty. If anyone likes that **** I think it's because theyre a WASP lured in by "atmosphere" and the idea of hand crafted cocktails being so much better than a cranberry and vodka on happy hour. If you like cocktails that challenge a bartenders craftsmanship, this is a fine place. But don't eat the food, go to a drive through on the way home and get food you regret for half the price

Music volume was wayyyyyyy too loud. 5 star cocktails and bartenders. Great music selection and great bar food, but had to yell just to talk to the person sitting next to me and my ears are ringing like I was at a club the next morning.
Small excellent menu and great drinks.

Absolutely incredible. Wonderful atmosphere and friendly staff. Great drinks and outstanding food. The vegan options are just as good as the meat options. Love sitting outside to people watch. Great place to get a drink with those you love.
Atmosphere is great. Drinks are crafty and well made. Missing 1 star because tots shouldn't be $5.
Good chill place to meet a friend for a drink
Get the burger

Cry Baby’s is great!!  This new bar has a casual speakeasy vibe. The clientele is a diverse, slightly older crowd (late 20s) and the drinks are well priced.  Plenty of room at the bar and lots of seating means that even on a crowded weekend you will be able to find some space.  We tried the shrimp (brave, I know) and they turned out to be better than expected!  Definitely give Cry Baby’s a stop on your night out in Downtown Gainesville.
Nice drinks.  Good food.  Had a good experience both times.
Huge spirits selection and excellent bartenders. The food is great as well

Fantastic bar. The inside is beautiful—a lovely bar area, nice seating, clean bathrooms + the water station is NICE. Great vibe inside (love the vinyl playing). Incredibly nice staff just makes this all the better. On top of this, it has great outdoor seating. Even though it's seated at the busiest intersection in Gainesville, sitting outside feels like its nice own world (it doesn't seem like you're sitting at the corner of a busy intersection at all). This will be a regular spot for me. I can't recommend it enough.
Great location, but a bit pricey for drinks.
Great drinks

Drinks and atmosphere were good, but my God, the service was so bad. Bartenders were rude, slow, and inefficient. One took my order and simply forgot to do it (not hard, a draft beer), the other accused me of taking is 6 cent pen when I went to pay the bill... Not even a busy night. Perhaps with some training of the staff this place could be better.
Awesome new bar in town.  They had a great cocktail list, new and innovative ideas, as well as awesome food items. I'm very excited for this new bar and to see how much it grows after opening.
Shut up and go
Great food and great atmosphere
You won't miss anything if you skip this place. Limited menu overpriced drinks and shabby decor.
Delicious drinks!
Pretty decent. Good bartenders! Great prices.

A craft cocktail bar with amazing food. The place has a cool vintage atmosphere and a few games for patrons to play. Their gin fizz and paloma are delicious, well-balanced drinks. A great location for late-night food, including a bucket of fried chicken, which is amazing. The drinks are on the more expensive side but they're well made and fairly priced in my opinion.
Meh. Inflated drink prices. Underwhelming decor. Prickly tables.
This place is cool af. Neighborhood Bar and Grill that this town needed. 5 stars.
